 UAW's Southern Gamble makes clear that the UAW's failed campaigns in the South can teach hard-won lessons about challenging the structural and legal roadblocks to union participation and effectively organizing workers within and beyond the auto industry.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aInternational labor activitieszSouthern StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aInternational labor activitieszSouthern StatesxHistoryy21st century. 0aLabor unionsxLaw and legislationzSouthern StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aLabor unionsxLaw and legislationzSouthern StatesxHistoryy21st century. 4aPolitical Science & Political History. 4aSOCIOLOGY & SOCIAL SCIENCE. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Labor & Industrial Relations.2bisacsh  aunion organizing in the South, transnational union cooperation, UAW, automobile transplants, UAW and foreign union leaders, unionization drives, union avoidance playbook.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311075183308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2023 Englishz978311131925408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2023z9783111318677oZDB-23-PLW40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781501769726?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501769726423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501769726/original  a978-3-11-075183-3  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131925-4  EBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Engl